race.comment: ONLY THE BEST (3) turned in a fine effort to win by 1.5L this course and distance, continuing his outstanding recent form. Races forward and he can salute again. MIDNIGHT HUSTLE (5) resumes and has switched from a Victorian stable. Won first-up last time in work over 1105m at Sale. That form would see him right in this. BLACK ZOUS (4) returns from a layoff of three months. He filled a minor placing when returning from a spell last preparation over 1100m at Darwin. The fresh form overall is sharp and he should be right in the finish. QUANAPIRRI BAY (2) is third-up and back in grade. The rail is a plus, but his figures suggest he'll have to settle for minor spoils here.
